notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-04T19:20:51.932Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-04 metadata backfill pass (this audit) completed the full scope: (1) charter bodies + risk/confidence on the milestone pm-doxj and all 11 open epics — each charter records scope in/out, standing invariants, closed-children count, and the live open-children inventory; (2) full-context bodies (Context / Approach or Design / Definition of done) + risk/confidence on all 24 open leaf items; (3) dep edges wired: pm-114v blocked_by pm-8t5x + related pm-2muu, pm-bgcu related pm-2muu (singleton locks reuse the lock machinery); (4) idea promotion: pm claim --next extracted from pm-8t5x prose into tracked Feature pm-114v under pm-dj98. Verification sweep after the pass: 41/41 active items have AC + estimate + priority + body + risk + confidence; every non-container item has a parent. Comments/linked-artifact reconciliation intentionally NOT duplicated here: the 146 missing / 134 orphaned linked-file rows remain owned by pm-j8z6, terminal-item resolution backfill by pm-e9zh."
close_reason: "Backfill complete: full-context bodies, risk and confidence now cover every active item; context is rebuildable from the pm CLI alone (verified by sweep, 2026-07-04)."
body: "## Context\n2026-07-04 metadata-utilization scan: 33 of 39 active items have an empty `body`, and most non-epic items have zero comments. Stefan's directive: ALL pm item metadata surfaces (body, comments, AC, deps, linked files/tests/docs, risk/confidence, resolution fields) must be fully utilized — a fresh agent must be able to rebuild its entire working context from the pm CLI alone, with no reliance on chat history, agent memory, or git archaeology.\n\n## Scope\nFor every ACTIVE item (open/in_progress), backfill:\n- `body`: full investigation/design narrative — root cause, constraints, alternatives considered, current state, evidence pointers. Descriptions stay as the one-paragraph summary; bodies carry the depth.\n- `pm comments`: decision/handoff-shaped context where it exists (review findings, mid-work decisions, session handoffs).\n- `risk`/`confidence` where meaningful; `pm deps` edges where items interact; linked files/tests/docs for every artifact the item touches.\n\nEmpty-body items as of scan: pm-3wsi, pm-mpbb, pm-o2kc, pm-ydp6, pm-5k4v, pm-8jdc, pm-5oj5, pm-u9d0, pm-ugqx, pm-dj98, pm-7zs0, pm-e9zh, pm-j8z6, pm-qt5d, pm-lt6n, pm-96wm, pm-28cf, pm-z5nb, pm-rj3w, pm-ghf1, pm-bgcu, pm-khdq, pm-jt3b, pm-ueuq, pm-gdi7, pm-jqd2, pm-92if, pm-b3e9, pm-llrp, pm-zwib, pm-ixoa, pm-l98s, pm-f4yn, pm-esbt.\n\n## Constraints\n- Active items only — do NOT touch closed items (changelog buckets by updated_at; renames/edits drag them into [Unreleased]).\n- Source each body from live verification (code, git history, session topic memory, GH issues/PRs), never from guesswork; concurrency trio pm-bgcu/pm-khdq/pm-zwib should carry the 2026-07-03 audit repro details.\n- This is tracker-only work; keep it out of unrelated code PRs."
